 "wikitext": "<choose uncached>\n<option weight=\"19\">\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:Level 64: “Ecological Miasma / Underground Pollution”}}\n<div class=\"meg-fandom-logoblock\">\n<center><big><big>'''READER ADVISORY: MISSING INFORMATION'''</big></big></center><br>\n\n<center>This article contains unverified details and missing information.<br><br>\n\nAs the final level below 100 to be documented, '''Level 64''' was discovered after an unusually long lapse. As a result, many of the level's key characteristics are either insufficiently documented or unavailable.\n\nTreat this article as a hazard notice. Do not attempt entry based on this document alone. If you believe to have encountered an entrance, discontinue travel and submit a report through approved channels. Assume all claims are unreliable until independently confirmed.\n</center></div><br>\n\n{{Class 5|color-h=255|color-s=20%|color-l=40%|entity=Sparsely Dispersed Entities}}\n{{Blurimage|file=Entrance to level -6.png|caption=An image of Level 64. The light above leads to [[Level 630]].}}</div>\n==Description==\n'''Level 64''' is a sprawling subterranean network of oversized chambers, unusually high ceilings, and contaminated lakes of water. Although the cave system is shrouded in a bioluminescent purple glow, visibility remains limited. The light fails to carry into wider chambers, and instead disperses into a weak haze that blurs distant features. This haze can give the false impression of open space, hiding drop-offs and shoreline edges until wanderers are within a few metres.\n\nThe expansive structure causes extreme reverberation, allowing low-volume sounds to travel across long distances and persist as overlapping echoes. Repeated exposure has been associated with severe tinnitus, fatigue, and in rarer instances, permanent hearing loss; it's advised that wanderers minimize verbal communication, secure loose equipment, and avoid using auditory cues as a method of navigation.\n\n'''Level 64''' is the first documented instance of [[Level 630]] infecting another level. Available evidence shows that a high-volume influx of [[Object 3|nuclear infection]] breached into '''Level 64''', causing an environmental degradation that rapidly accelerated. The level was discovered and documented only after ecological collapse, so any reliable information about its pre-infection period is not available. There have been attempts to examine the rock sedimentation and overall environment to learn what the level originally looked like, but the sheer danger of '''Level 64''' has rendered it almost impossible to create long-term studies.\n\nDue to the presence of [[Object 3|nuclear infection]], the air quality is extremely toxic, producing harmful fumes that become trapped by the cavern's interior. These fumes contain a microorganism known as a \"[[Object 3|verdbear]],\" a type of airborne bacterium capable of surviving in environments affected by [[Object 3|nuclear infection]]. Verdbears replicate very quickly, primarily in the pulmonary tissues when fumes are inhaled, and may contribute to systemic infection in individuals already compromised by [[Object 3|nuclear infection]].\n\nDespite the enclosed, subterranean layout, intermittent bursts of wind have been documented. These currents present as brief, low-intensity gales that funnel through connecting chambers, where they circulate unpredictably before dissipating. While the airflow isn’t forceful enough to hinder movement, it’s sufficient in disturbing the level’s stagnant environment by redistributing the fumes produced by [[Object 3|nuclear infection]] into new pockets of the cave.\n==Entities==\nDespite the level's extreme hazards, entities (e.g. [[Entity 10|skin-stealers]], [[Entity 5|hounds]]) are not absent, and they're usually encountered in irregular pockets rather than as stable populations. Most sightings are reported near known entrances and exits, suggesting recent entry from adjacent levels, and typically linger long enough to scavenge, orient themselves, or pursue easy prey before the toxic environment force them to retreat. \n===The Nuclear Membri===\n<div class=\"meg-fandom-logoblock\">\n<center><big><big>'''ERROR 401: UNAUTHORIZED'''</big></big></center><br>\n\n<center>'''Reason:''' The following information is awaiting for approval to be published.<br><br>\n</center></div>\n==Colonies and Outposts==\n'''Level 64''' likely had no settlements prior to its contamination; it was the final sub-100 level to be documented, and whether '''Level 64''' was even habitable in the first place still remains ambiguous.\n\nEfforts to establish a long-term sustainable colony within the level is physically impossible. There was, however, a temporary base used by scientists for experimenting with [[Object 3|nuclear infection]].\n===Outpost 64===\n*Small group of 4 scientists.\n*Abandoned; was active during 2020.\n*Main purpose was to discover and learn more about the anomalous properties of [[Object 3|nuclear infection]]. Their experiments have been recorded, and later replicated. Future tests produced similar results, even with different variables. This was the first, and only successful experiment in '''Level 64.'''\n<div style=\"background-color:#000000; color: white; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:2px dotted #FFFFFF; border-radius: 3px\">\n\n{{Collapse|num=1|initial=> '''Experiment One: Low Temperatures'''|final=< '''Experiment One: Low Temperatures'''|body=\nA one-cup sample of '''Object 3''' was placed inside an icebox. When the container was opened, there was no ice formation nor water in the box. The sample volume had noticeably tripled its original size, and the bottom of the icebox showed localized searing.}}\n----\n{{Collapse|num=2|initial=> '''Experiment Two: High Temperatures'''|final=< '''Experiment Two: High Temperatures'''|body=\nA one-cup sample was introduced to a boiling pot, and disappeared shortly after contact. Deterioration occurred faster than anticipated, and the result is consistent with '''Object 3's''' inability to be stored in typical containers due to rapid material dissolution. \n\nHigh-temperature materials do not neutralize nor hinder the substance, and later experiments reveal that verdbears actually replicate twice as fast when exposed to hot temperatures.}}\n----\n{{Collapse|num=3|initial=> '''Experiment Three: Level Resistance'''|final=< '''Experiment Three: Level Resistance'''|body=\nA one-cup sample was poured across a partition wall with similar resistance to [[Level 0]]'s walls. Structural integrity declined before collapsing in less than an hour. Deterioration was observed to accelerate as the affected area expanded, suggesting that '''Object 3''' spreads exponentially.}}\n----\n{{Collapse|num=4|initial=> '''Experiment Four: Entities'''|final=< '''Experiment Four: Entities'''|body=\nA bucket volume dose was applied directly to a [[Entity 4|deathmoth]] to evaluate entity response. No behavioural adaptation was recorded; however, the entity exhibited rapid deformation. Its wings softened and \"melted\" into the torso, internal organs visibly bloated to abnormal sizes, and the grey body hairs withered and detached within minutes. The deathmoth died following exposure.\n\nThe deformation did not resemble the \"mutated phenotype\" associated with '''Object 3''' (e.g., the [[Entity 62|Nuclear Membri]]). This suggests transformation is not the default outcome of exposure, and may be limited to a select number of entities, or to a narrow set of conditions that were not met during the trial.}}\n----\n{{Collapse|num=5|initial=> '''Experiment Five: Neutralized Entities'''|final=< '''Experiment Five: Neutralized Entities'''|body=\nA bucket volume dose was applied over a neutralized [[Entity 10|skin-stealer]] to evaluate persistence of biological residue. Over approximately a week, the remains dissolved until no intact matter was observed. Unlike the death moth trial, no deformation or partial conversion was recorded. The dissolution of the body was a breakdown of inactive tissue rather than structural reshaping.}}\n</div>\n==Entrances and Exits==\n===Entrances===\n*Jumping onto a manhole in the streets of [[Level 63]].\n*Travelling below [[Level 630]]'s surface will directly bring you to '''Level 64'''.\n*Crawling through specific narrow spaces on [[Level 8]].\n*Pressing '''64''' on an elevator in [[Level 22]] will bring you here.<ref>The button for '''Level 64''' did not exist prior to its discovery.</ref>\n===Exits===\n*Entering the surface will bring wanderers to [[Level 630]].\n*Noclipping into a wall will lead to [[Level 65]].\n*Unknown factors can bring wanderers to [[Level 87]].\n*Cramped tunnels may lead to [[Level 8]] or [[Level 117]].\n\n{{Footnotes}}\n</option>\n<option weight=\"1\">\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:Level -1000: {NO DATA} }}\n<div class=\"meg-fandom-logoblock\"; text-align:left; letter-spacing:1px; margin:5px; border:1.5px solid white; border-radius:5px; padding:10px; font-size:1.1em;\">\n<center><big><big>'''Error 404: Page Not Found'''</big></big></center><br>\n\n<center>Error fetching level data for: \"'''Level -1000'''\".<br><br>\n\nReason: Unrecognized character: \"...el '''-'''100...\"<br>\n\nPerhaps you were looking for another page?<br>\n</center>\n</div>\n</option>\n</choose>\n\n{{Redirect|Prev=63|Next=65}}\n{{LinkCollapse|num=6|initial='''> Open Author & Credits'''|final='''v Close Author & Credits'''|body=\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">'''Author''': [[User:Homie Robot|Homie Robot]]</div>\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">'''First, Third, and Current Rewriter''': [[User:Homie Robot|Homie Robot]]</div>\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">'''Second Rewriter''': [[User:PuppyBorkbutaccountgotwiped|PuppyBork]]</div>\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">Image heavily edited by [[User:Homie Robot|Homie Robot]]</div><br>\n\n'''[https://backrooms.fandom.com/wiki/Level_64?direction=next&oldid=772449 An older revision (rewrite 3) can be found here.]'''<br>\n'''[https://backrooms.fandom.com/wiki/Level_64?direction=prev&oldid=772449 An even older revision (rewrite 2) can be found here.]'''<br>\n'''[https://backrooms.fandom.com/wiki/Level_64?direction=next&oldid=374665 An even even older revision (rewrite 1) can be found here.]'''<br>\n'''[https://backrooms.fandom.com/wiki/Level_64?oldid=369411 An even even even older revision (original page) can be found here.]'''<br>\n\n<center>[[file:Astolfo.gif|150px]]</center><br>\n\n{{:User:Homie Robot/BookofRevelations}}\n\n}}\n{{User:Homie Robot/Level 64 Theme}}\n\n[[Category:Class 5]]\n[[Category:Levels]]\n[[Category:Cluster I]]\n[[Category:Infected]]\n[[Category:Dangerous]]\n[[zh:Level 64]]"
